control procedures for data communication-an asa progress report.wsectional committee x. of the american standardsassociation, has charged one of its task groups, x.., with the responsibility to "define and specifyfunctional control requirements and characteristics governing the operation of digital data generating andreceiving systems interconnected by communication system."  this effort is primarily directed toward systemsemploying the american standard code for information interchange (ascii).  this paper represents a progressreport on the work of this group toward a proposal for national and international standardization in thefield of control procedures.  it describes both the old and new work of the task group.  the new workis presented in detail, while the work that has been presented in earlier papers ["control procedures fordata communication," task group document x../, may : "transparent-mode control procedures for datacommunication," task group document x../, december, : comm. acm  (apr. ), -; "controlprocedures for data communications," task group document x../, march, ] is retained herein summary form.  many of the concepts and principles described herein have been submitted to the internationalorganization for standardization via earlier papers and are now embodied in working papers of that organization. cacm february, cajb march ,   : pm